386→                        <div id="content">Let $F(n)$ be the maximum possible size of a subset $A\subseteq\{1,\ldots,N\}$ such that the products $ab$ are distinct for all $a&#60;b$. Is there a constant $c$ such that\[F(n)=\pi(n)+(c+o(1))n^{3/4}(\log n)^{-3/2}?\]If $A\subseteq \{1,\ldots,n\}$ is such that all products $a_1\cdots a_r$ are distinct for $a_1&#60;\cdots &#60;a_r$ then is it true that\[\lvert A\rvert \leq \pi(n)+O(n^{\frac{r+1}{2r}})?\]</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/425">#425</a>: <a href="#cite-Er69-425" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er69','425'); return false;">[Er69]</a><a href="#cite-Er70b-425" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er70b','425'); return false;">[Er70b]</a><a href="#cite-Er73-425" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er73','425'); return false;">[Er73]</a><a href="#cite-Er77c-425" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er77c','425'); return false;">[Er77c]</a><a href="#cite-ErGr80-425" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('ErGr80','425'); return false;">[ErGr80,p.84]</a></div>
